(1) y = x² + 3x + 2;
(2) y = 1 - x³ - x⁴ - 2x⁵;
(3) y = sin 2x + cos(x/2) + tan x.

Which of the following functions are periodic?
(1) y = sin²x; (2) y = sin x²; (3) y = x cos x;
(4) y = sin(1/x); (5) y = 1 + tan x; (6) y = 5;
(7) y = E(x); (8) y = x - E(x).
(The function E(x) is defined thus: if x is an integer, E(x) = x; if x is not an integer, E(x) is the greatest integer less than x. Thus E(2) = 2; E(3.25) = 3; E(-1.37) = -2.)

